(424, 1, '2015-08-30 01:39:34', '2015-08-30 01:39:34', 'You play the lotto your way, I play the lotto my way, but what''s the best way to play?\r\n\r\nTo start with you can leave it to luck or you can leave it to math. Now there''s countless books and systems giving you  hodge podge ways to pick your numbers, then there''s statistical analysis.  Since math explains the world I choose to go with the latter.  When I pick my numbers I use a proven system that I created, a system that has predicted 6/6 numbers from a number set as low as 25 over 140 times. <strong>That''s right, I have successfully predicted 140 Jackpot Winners worth over $500 Million dollars. </strong>\r\n\r\nWhen I was a freshman in college I started working on a statistical analysis program to analyse the lottery data for Indiana. Since then I have mastered math, programming, logic, and yes, THE LOTTO. Here''s just a small chunk of the data my program takes in to consideration when predicting my number set and picking my numbers.\r\n<blockquote>Total Draws: 2007\r\nReading draw data...\r\n==============\r\nAverage picks: 250\r\nOOOOOO: 32 | 0.015944195316392625 Last Since: 17 Average Between: 61\r\nOEEEEE: 161 | 0.0802192326856004 Last Since: 21 Average Between: 11\r\nOOEEEE: 481 | 0.23966118584952667 Last Since: 1 Average Between: 3\r\nOOOEEE: 648 | 0.32286995515695066 Last Since: 0 Average Between: 2\r\nOOOOEE: 497 | 0.24763328350772296 Last Since: 7 Average Between: 3\r\nOOOOOE: 158 | 0.0787244643746886 Last Since: 13 Average Between: 11\r\nEEEEEE: 30 | 0.014947683109118086 Last Since: 75 Average Between: 63</blockquote>\r\nWhat does all this mean? Can''t look at it an figure it out? Maybe you should look over the lessons that are part of every membership (YES, even the FREE ones). I''ll teach you several tips and tricks to increase your odds of wining and <strong>Pick Smarter</strong> so you can <strong>Win More</strong>', 'Odd or Even?', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '420-autosave-v1', 